Usage: sh makeBAM <pbam> <ref> <tmp> <prompt>

input: <pbam>, name of the pbam file before the exttension; make sure the diff file has the same name and is in the same folder
<ref>: reference genome or transcriptome with path 
<tmp>: name of the tmp folder (will be automatically deleted)
<prompt>: options: genome is for genome aligned pbams, transcriptome is for transcriptome alined pbams

output: <bam>, a bam file that has the same name as pbam and diff (with a bam extension) 
